description:
Responsibilities:

Responsible for products sourcing and trading;
Liaison with customers and suppliers to achieve sales target;
Develop new suppliers and products;
Negotiate and build relationship with buyers and sellers;
Follow up contract issuance, shipments, payments and other trade related matters;
Liaise with internal departments for trade operation matters.

Requirements:

Degree / Diploma holder in Purchasing / Trading / Sourcing / Business related discipline preferable;
Minimum 3 years solid trading and sourcing experience in any one of below categories: Food & beverage / FMCG;    
Experience in food associated would be an added advantage;
Hardworking, independent and self-motivated with excellent communication skills;
Candidates with trading experience in other categories will also be considered;
Candidate with less experience but passionate in food & beverage industry will be considered as Assistant Trading Executive.

Staff Benefit:

13-month Salary
Yearly Discretionary Bonus
Medical Insurance
Annual Leave
Payable Sick Leave
Birthday Leave
Encourage continuing education and on-job training
Open office working environment
Offer promotion opportunities and long-term career path

  工作職責:
負責做好各類行政檔案、資料的收發轉遞工作；負責保管有關行政方面的文書、檔案材料；做好辦公室日常行政事務及文秘工作;
工作要求:
F5以上學歷,熟練使用各種辦公軟體，有良好的團隊協作精神、服務意識以及較強的交流溝通能力與組織協調能力;
工作時間: 星期一至星期五,9:30AM-6:30PM
有意者請按Apply Now申請

Responsibilities:

Reporting to the merchandising manager, the candidate will engage in product development, sourcing, sampling, showroom setup, photo quotation and order follow up in the seasonal ornament division.

Requirements:

An ideal candidate should possess the following qualifications and competences: 

School certificate/diploma or degree from recognized institutions;
Min. 2 years experience in merchandising tasks, preferably in seasonal ornament or related fields;
Self-motivated, responsible, diligent and organized challenger taker;
Good communication, negotiation, and problem solving skills;
Good command of English and Putonghua is preferred;
Familiar with MS Office and Chinese Word Processing;
Knowledge of Photoshop/AI will be an advantage.

About us:

Please visit www.EAornament.com.hk for our details

Career Development:

Right candidate will start the career in the post of assistant merchandiser/merchandiser, and will get promote to merchandiser/senior merchandiser if he/she performs well and make contributes to the company. 

Our offer:

We offer five-day work with flexible working hours and attractive benefits including double pay, year end bonus, bank holidays, up to 16 days annual leave, medical allowance, and dental allowance.

Interested candidates could apply for the above job opening by clicking APPLY NOW or send CV to info(at)eaornament.com.hk.  Please do include your current and expected salaries and date of availability in the resume. 

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

What we are looking for:

Collaborate with market leads, sales, design & factories for successful product launch campaigns. Support new product introduction projects to success in accordance with defined targets, strategies, and goals.



What You Will Own & How You Will Make A Difference:

Liaise with market leads, sales, design, quality, and factories on the evaluation of component & product specification and quality requirement;
Coordinate and support sample preparation activities for packaging development, qualification test and marketing purposes, etc.;
Monitor packaging development to meet specific packaging requirements;
Execute project plan for the assigned projects;
Monitor, track, and provide an update on the project progress;
Work with related parties for project changes. Manage and execute changes to achieve project outputs and goals;
Perform other duties as assigned.



Who You Are:

Tertiary education or above;
2 years or above working experience. Experiences in project management or related duties preferred but not essential;
Good command of written and spoken in English and Chinese;
Good communication skills and project management skills;
Proficient in MS Project, MS Word, MS Excel & MS PowerPoint.

What we are looking for:

We are looking for a competitive and trustworthy Sales Executive to help us maintain a good relationship with current customers and keep an eye on market trends and potentials to explore new businesses.



What You Will Own & How You Will Make A Difference:

Manage existing accounts, experience in handling the US market is an advantage;
Work closely and independently with overseas customers in sales activities;
Meet customers regularly;
Demonstrate and present products;
Maintain accurate records;
Review sales performance and explore new business potential;
Ensure high levels of customer satisfaction;
Liaise with internal stakeholders from concept through production stage;
Perform such other duties as may be assigned.


Who You Are:

Diploma or above in any disciplines;
At least 2 years relevant experience in household merchandise;
Experience in handling the US market is an advantage;
Strong interpersonal and communication skills;
Good team player, a strong sense of responsibility;
Mature, well organized, and detailed mind;
Able to excel in a fast-paced and dynamic environment with tight deadlines;
Good command of English & fluency in speaking English & Putonghua.
** Candidates with more experience will be considered as Senior Sales Executive.

Responsibilities:
Identify training needs, design, deliver training programs for front-line staff to enhance and polish customer services skill, product knowledge, and drive the Company culture;
Evaluate training effectiveness by monitoring retail staff product knowledge through frequent shop visit;
Create fun and exciting learning programs or projects for team enhancement;
Assist in developing and maintaining e-learning platforms;
Maintain and update training materials and record, prepare training statistics and reports in regular basis;
Other ad hoc L&D projects when necessary.
Requirements:
Degree holder in Human Resources Management or related discipline;
At least 2-3 years’ relevant working experience preferably in retail;
Proactive learner with positive and can do attitude;
Responsible, flexible and able to work in a fast-paced environment;
Proficient in video editing, Excel, PowerPoint, Chinese word processing;
Good command of written and spoken English, Cantonese and Putonghua;
Candidate with less experience will be considered as Assistant Training Officer.

Our remuneration packages will be commensurate with your QUALITY.

Please send your application with current and expected salary, and quote the relevant reference number on the subject by clicking "Apply Now".

All information provided will be treated in strict confidence and used for recruitment purposes only.

Responsibilities:

Responsible for products sourcing and trading;
Liaison with customers and suppliers to achieve sales target;
Develop new suppliers and products;
Negotiate and build relationship with buyers and sellers;
Follow up contract issuance, shipments, payments and other trade related matters;
Liaise with internal departments for trade operation matters. 

Requirements:

Degree / Diploma holder in Purchasing / Trading / Sourcing / Business related discipline preferable;
Solid trading and sourcing experience will be an advantage;
Hardworking, independent and self-motivated with excellent communication skills 

Staff Benefit:

13-month Salary
Yearly Discretionary Bonus
Medical Insurance
Payable Sick Leave
Birthday Leave

What We Are Looking For:

To oversee accounts and work directly with marketing companies and clients on the development of product & pricing strategy;
To make sure everything goes well from product development, pricing to delivery of goods;
To handle post-delivery issues such as quality complaints, customer chargebacks, payment;
To manage & maintain product and data information within company systems (Global Vision).


 What You Will Own & How You Will Make A Difference:

To maintain & update cost/pricing files;
To liaise with Costing Department on product costs;
To prepare and submit quotations to marketing arms/direct customers;
To follow up Clients Day-to-Day issues;
To attend customers’ meetings to perform duty and aid business;
To closely monitor customer’s chargebacks & overdue payments;
To be responsible for supporting product development;
To complete forms, e.g., new customer & new item set up;
To define/amend product specifications on new/existing products
To monitor communication between marketing arms/direct customers & factories;
To manage & maintain product and data information within company systems;
To attend training/seminar to develop relevant knowledge, techniques, and skills;
To perform & complete jobs & projects as requested;
To supervise supporting staff (if any).

 
Who You Are: 

University graduate, min 3 years relevant working experience;
Excellent command of both English and Chinese;
Proficiency in MS Office and PC knowledge;
Able to work under pressure and independently;
Be Initiative, responsible, and have a sense of leadership;
Strong organizing capability, effective presentation and communication skills;
Good marketing sense, creative with an analytical mind.
